**Lecture 4.2**    
* [Liu, X. et al. (1996)](http://www.univie.ac.at/ibmz/student/results/apoptosis5.pdf). Induction of apoptotic program in cell-free extracts: requirement for dATP and cytochrome c. Cell, 86(1), 147-157.  
  
* [Li, P. et al. (1997)](http://www.univie.ac.at/ibmz/student/results/apoptosis2.pdf). Cytochrome c and dATP-Dependent Formation of Apaf-1/Caspase-9 Complex Initiates an Apoptotic Protease Cascade. Cell, 91(4), 479-489.  
    
* [Yuan, S. et al. (2010)](http://www.cell.com/structure/retrieve/pii/S0969212610001346). Structure of an apoptosome-procaspase-9 CARD complex. Structure, 18(5), 571-583.  
  
**Lecture 4.3**  
* [Muchmore, S.W. et al. (1996)](http://www.nature.com/nature/journal/v381/n6580/abs/381335a0.html). X-ray and NMR structure of human Bcl-xL, an inhibitor of programmed cell death. Nature, 381(6580), 335-341.  
  
* [Chou, J.J. et al. (1999)](https://yuan.med.harvard.edu/sites/yuan.med.harvard.edu/files/19_Cell1999_Solution%20structure_BID.pdf). Solution structure of BID, an intracellular amplifier of apoptotic signaling. Cell, 96(5), 615-624.  
  
* [Suzuki, M. et al. (2000)](http://www.cell.com/retrieve/pii/S0092867400001677). Structure of Bax: coregulation of dimer formation and intracellular localization. Cell, 103(4), 645-654.  
  
* [Antonsson, B. et al. (1997)](http://www.sciencemag.org/content/277/5324/370). Inhibition of Bax channel-forming activity by Bcl-2. Science, 277(5324), 370-372.  
  
* [Minn, A.J. et al. (1997)](http://dx.doi.org/10.1038/385353a0). Bcl-x(L) forms an ion channel in synthetic lipid membranes. Nature, 385(6614), 353-357.  
  
* [Schendel, S.L. et al. (1997)](http://www.pnas.org/content/94/10/5113) (Lecture 4.3). Channel formation by antiapoptotic protein Bcl-2. Proc Natl Acad Sci U.S.A., 94(10), 5113-5118.  
  
* [Schlesinger, P.H. et al. (1997)](http://www.pnas.org/content/94/21/11357). Comparison of the ion channel characteristics of proapoptotic BAX and antiapoptotic BCL-2. Proc Natl Acad Sci U.S.A., 94(21), 11357-11362.  
  
* [Peixoto, P.M. et al. (2009)](http://www.biochemj.org/bj/423/bj4230381.htm). MAC inhibitors suppress mitochondrial apoptosis. Biochem J., 423(3), 381-387.  
  
* [Czabotar, P.E. et al. (2013)](http://www.cell.com/retrieve/pii/S009286741201553X). Bax crystal structures reveal how BH3 domains activate Bax and nucleate its oligomerization to induce apoptosis. Cell, 152(3), 519-531.  
  
* [Kushnareva, Y. et al. (2012)](http://dx.doi.org/10.1371/journal.pbio.1001394). Bax activation initiates the assembly of a multimeric catalyst that facilitates Bax pore formation in mitochondrial outer membranes. PLoS Biol, 10(9), e1001394.  
  
**Lecture 4.4**  
* [Qi, S. et al. (2010)](http://www.cell.com/retrieve/pii/S0092867410002904). Crystal structure of the Caenorhabditis elegans apoptosome reveals an octameric assembly of CED-4. Cell, 141(3), 446-457.  
  
* [Woo, J.S. et al. (2003)](http://dx.doi.org/10.1038/sj.cdd.4401303). Unique structural features of a BCL-2 family protein CED-9 and biophysical characterization of CED-9/EGL-1 interactions. Cell Death Differ, 10(12), 1310-1319.  
  
* [Yan, N. et al. (2004)](http://dx.doi.org/10.1016/j.molcel.2004.08.022). Structural, biochemical, and functional analyses of CED-9 recognition by the proapoptotic proteins EGL-1 and CED-4. Mol Cell, 15(6), 999-1006.  
  
* [Yan, N. et al. (2005)](http://dx.doi.org/10.1038/nature04002). Structure of the CED-4-CED-9 complex provides insights into programmed cell death in Caenorhabditis elegans. Nature, 437(7060), 831-837.  
  
* [Wang, X. et al. (2002)](https://mcdb.colorado.edu/labs1/xue/PDF%20Files/WAH-1.pdf). Mechanisms of AIF-mediated apoptotic DNA degradation in Caenorhabditis elegans. Science, 298(5598), 1587-1892.  

